1. Liquidity
Is NetLiq YoY >0? (Long-term trend)
Is NetLiq>SMA(21 days)? (Immediate momentum/turning point)

2. Credit & Stress Pillar (30 Points) – "The Foundation"
Is HY Spread Z-Score<0.5? (Credit is stable)

3. Valuation & Real Rates (20 Points) – "The Gravity"
Is Real 10Y<1.5%? (Low gravity/High multiples justified)
Is Real M2 Growth>−2%? (Structural money isn't collapsing)

4. Volatility Filter (10 Points) – "The Guardrail"
Test G: Is VIX<SMA(20 days)?

After 2022 bear market challenge
The Deceleration Penalty: Instead of checking if Liquidity is $>0$, we now check if the Growth Rate is slowing down. If Liquidity growth today is lower than it was 3 months ago, you lose points. This catches the "Peak" months before the "Crash."The 200-Day Guardrail: We have added the S&P 500 vs. its 200-day Moving Average as a mandatory filter. If the price breaks the 200-day SMA, the maximum possible allocation is capped at 40%, regardless of how good the liquidity looks.Tightened Thresholds:Real 10Y: Threshold lowered from $1.5\%$ to $1.0\%$. (1.5% was too late for the 2022 rate shock).HY Spread: Threshold lowered from $0.5$ to $0.0$. (If credit is even slightly worse than its 3-year average, we reduce exposure).M2 Real Growth: Now requires $>0\%$ growth to be bullish (previously $-2\%$).